                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700711-34-victim447 t17700711-34-viclabel179"></join>, and live in Monmouth-street: I keep a stable in <placeName id="t17700711-34-crimeloc180">Brown's gardens</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17700711-34-crimeloc180" type="placeName" value="Brown's gardens"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17700711-34-crimeloc180" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700711-34-off177 t17700711-34-crimeloc180"></join>: we have a hole cut in the door for the pole of the coach to come through. I put my coach in the coach-house, and hung up my great coat. I went the next morning for my coat; a boy met me, and told me he had seen a boy come out of my stable with my coat. I took the prisoner the Tuesday following; he fell a crying: he told me, he went in at the hole, and took my coat, and sold it to an old clothes-man for 2 s. and offered me two guineas to make it up, which I would not do.</p>
